📊 Python Inventory & Revenue Analysis Project
🔹 Objective
Analyze the relationship between demand, inventory (stockouts), and revenue using Python to identify inefficiencies and uncover opportunities for revenue growth.

🔹 Tools
Python (Pandas, NumPy)
Data Visualization (Matplotlib / Seaborn Bubble Chart)
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

🔹 Key Insights
📦 Demand vs Supply Imbalance
Multiple brands show high stockout rates, meaning products are frequently unavailable
Indicates inventory planning is not aligned with demand
Stockouts directly result in lost sales, not delayed purchases

💰 Lost Revenue is Highly Concentrated
A small number of brands account for most of the lost revenue
Revenue loss is driven more by scale (demand volume) than stockout rate alone
Even moderate stockouts can cause large losses when demand is high

📈 High-Price, High-Demand Opportunity
Some brands have high prices + high stockout rates
Indicates strong demand even at premium pricing
These represent high-margin growth opportunities if supply is increased

🔄 Low-Price, High-Volume Pressure
Lower-priced brands also show frequent stockouts
These are likely fast-moving, high-demand products
Critical for maintaining sales volume and customer traffic

📉 Overstock / Weak Demand Segments
Some higher-priced brands have low stockout rates
Suggests overstocking or weak demand
Leads to capital being tied up and risk of markdowns

⚖️ Core Market Stability
Most brands fall into a mid-price, moderate stockout range
Indicates a relatively balanced supply-demand relationship
Represents the core, stable segment of the business

📌 Strategic Recommendation
The business should prioritize inventory optimization based on revenue impact, not just stockout rates.
Key actions include:
Focus on high lost-revenue brands first → biggest immediate financial impact
Expand inventory for high-price, high-demand products to maximize margins
Stabilize stock for low-price, high-volume products to maintain consistent sales
Reduce overstock in weak-demand segments through pricing adjustments or promotions
Improve demand forecasting and supply chain alignment to prevent recurring stockouts

🚀 Key Takeaway
Not all stockouts are equally important — the highest impact comes from high-demand, high-revenue products. By prioritizing these areas, the business can reduce lost revenue, improve inventory efficiency, and drive scalable growth.


